cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.IR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely sub-category as the paper focuses on using deep learning models for image-based analysis of urban tree cover using Google Street View images. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of deep learning models for the analysis. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category as the paper discusses the use of advanced deep learning techniques for efficient estimation of urban metrics. 
4. cs.GR (Graphics) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with image-based analysis of urban tree cover. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible sub-category as the paper discusses the use of gradient-weighted class activation map (Grad-CAM) to interpret the features learned by the end-to-end model.
